msgstr "网格着色"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/smoothing.rst:9
msgid ""
"Example mesh rendered flat, smoothed using edge split, and using Subdivision "
"Surface. Note how edges are rendered differently. `Sample blend-file <https://"
"wiki.blender.org/index.php/:File:25-manual-meshsmooth-example.blend>`__."
msgstr ""
"平直的、拆边后光滑，以及使用表面细分后光滑的渲染后网格。注意边线渲染结果的差"
"异。 `范例文件 <https://wiki.blender.org/index.php/:File:25-manual-meshsmooth-"
"example.blend>`__。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/smoothing.rst:24
msgid ""
"As seen in the previous sections, polygons are central to Blender. Most objects "
"are represented by polygons and truly curved objects are often approximated by "
"polygon meshes. When rendering images, you may notice that these polygons "
"appear as a series of small, flat faces."
msgstr ""
"如同前文看到的，多边形对于Blender很重要。大多数物体是使用多边形表达的，并且真正"
"弯曲的物体也通常是使用多边形网格近似表示的。在渲染图像的时候，你可能注意到这些多"
"边形看起来像一系列小的平直面。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/smoothing.rst:29
msgid ""
"Sometimes this is a desirable effect, but usually we want our objects to look "
"nice and smooth. This section shows you how to visually smooth an object, and "
"how to apply the *Auto Smooth* filter to quickly and easily combine smooth and "
"faceted polygons in the same object."
msgstr ""
"有时候，这是期望的效果，但是通常我们更希望物体看起漂亮和光滑。这一节将展示如何在"
"视觉上对物体进行平滑化，以及如何使用 *自动光滑* 过滤选项来便捷地对同一个物体结合"
"使用光滑和平直的多边形。"

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/smoothing.rst:33
msgid ""
"The last section on this page shows possibilities for smoothing a mesh's "
"geometry, not only its appearance."
msgstr "这一页的最后一个部分展示了光滑网格几何结构，而非仅是外观的可能性。"

